* Static Member Variable *
    - Member variables qualified with static keyword
    - Not part of the object, but they are part of the class
    - Only one copy exists and is shared between objects

* Rules of usage *
    - are only declared inside the class.
    - have to be defined outside the class for initialization

* Static Member Functions *
    - functions qualified with static keyword
    - required only in declaration
    - belongs to class and not to objects
    - do not receive "this" pointer

!! Static Member Functions cannot access non-static members of the class !!